    "content": "<html lang=\"en\">\n<head>\n<meta charset=\"UTF-8\" />\n<meta name=\"viewport\" content=\"width=device-width, initial-scale=1\" />\n<title>SQL Concept Interactive Exploration</title>\n<style>\n  /* Minimal, basic: plain black on white, no colors, no animations */\n  body {\n    font-family: monospace, monospace;\n    margin: 10px;\n    background: white;\n    color: black;\n  }\n  textarea, input[type=text], select {\n    font-family: monospace, monospace;\n    font-size: 14px;\n    margin: 3px 0;\n    width: 100%;\n    box-sizing: border-box;\n  }\n  button {\n    font-family: monospace;\n    margin: 3px 2px 3px 0;\n  }\n  fieldset {\n    border: 1px solid black;\n    margin-bottom: 10px;\n    padding: 8px;\n  }\n  legend {\n    font-weight: bold;\n  }\n  label {\n    display: block;\n    margin-top: 5px;\n  }\n  #output {\n    white-space: pre-wrap;\n    border: 1px solid black;\n    padding: 6px;\n    min-height: 100px;\n    margin-top: 8px;\n    overflow: auto;\n    font-size: 13px;\n  }\n  #table-data {\n    margin-top: 8px;\n    border-collapse: collapse;\n    width: 100%;\n    font-size: 13px;\n  }\n  #table-data th, #table-data td {\n    border: 1px solid black;\n    padding: 3px 5px;\n    text-align: left;\n  }\n</style>\n</head>\n<body>\n<h1>SQL Concept Interactive Exploration</h1>\n\n<p>This interactive tool allows you to build, edit, and run simple SQL queries on example in-memory tables. Experiment with SQL concepts by:</p>\n<ul>\n  <li>Creating and modifying tables and their data</li>\n  <li>Writing SELECT queries with WHERE, JOIN, GROUP BY, HAVING, ORDER BY, LIMIT</li>\n  <li>Using aggregate functions (COUNT, SUM, AVG, MIN, MAX)</li>\n  <li>Seeing query results displayed as a table</li>\n  <li>Exploring SQL clauses through interactive controls</li>\n</ul>\n\n<fieldset>\n<legend>1. Define or Edit Table</legend>\n<label for=\"table-select\">Select a predefined example table or choose \"Custom\" to define your own:</label>\n<select id=\"table-select\" aria-label=\"Select example or custom table\">\n  <option value=\"employees\">Employees</option>\n  <option value=\"departments\">Departments</option>\n  <option value=\"orders\">Orders</option>\n  <option value=\"products\">Products</option>\n  <option value=\"custom\">Custom Table</option>\n</select>\n\n<div id=\"custom-table-editor\" style=\"display:none;\">\n  <label for=\"custom-table-name\">Custom Table Name:</label>\n  <input type=\"text\" id=\"custom-table-name\" placeholder=\"e.g. my_table\" aria-label=\"Custom table name\" />\n  <label for=\"custom-table-cols\">Column names (comma separated):</label>\n  <input type=\"text\" id=\"custom-table-cols\" placeholder=\"id,name,salary\" aria-label=\"Column names for custom table\" />\n  <label for=\"custom-table-data\">Data (rows separated by new lines, columns by commas):</label>\n  <textarea id=\"custom-table-data\" rows=\"6\" placeholder=\"1,John,50000\\n2,Alice,60000\\n3,Bob,55000\" aria-label=\"Table data input\"></textarea>\n  <button id=\"btn-load-custom-table\">Load Custom Table</button>\n  <div id=\"custom-table-status\" aria-live=\"polite\" style=\"margin-top:5px;\"></div>\n</div>\n</fieldset>\n\n<fieldset>\n<legend>2. Compose SQL Query (limited to SELECT statements)</legend>\n<label for=\"sql-query\">Write your SQL SELECT query here:</label>\n<textarea id=\"sql-query\" rows=\"8\" aria-label=\"SQL query input\"></textarea>\n\n<button id=\"btn-run-query\">Run Query</button>\n<button id=\"btn-clear-query\">Clear Query</button>\n<button id=\"btn-reset\">Reset All</button>\n</fieldset>\n\n<fieldset>\n<legend>3. Interactive Query Builder Controls</legend>\n\n<div id=\"interactive-builder\">\n\n  <label for=\"select-columns\">Select Columns (comma separated or * for all):</label>\n  <input type=\"text\" id=\"select-columns\" placeholder=\"*\" aria-label=\"Columns to SELECT\" />\n\n  <label for=\"where-conditions\">WHERE Conditions (e.g. salary > 50000 AND dept_id = 2):</label>\n  <input type=\"text\" id=\"where-conditions\" placeholder=\"\" aria-label=\"WHERE clause conditions\" />\n\n  <label for=\"join-type\">JOIN Type:</label>\n  <select id=\"join-type\" aria-label=\"Join type\">\n    <option value=\"none\">None</option>\n    <option value=\"inner\">INNER JOIN</option>\n    <option value=\"left\">LEFT JOIN</option>\n    <option value=\"right\">RIGHT JOIN</option>\n    <option value=\"full\">FULL OUTER JOIN</option>\n  </select>\n\n  <label for=\"join-table\">Join Table:</label>\n  <select id=\"join-table\" aria-label=\"Join table\">\n    <option value=\"\">--none--</option>\n    <option value=\"employees\">Employees</option>\n    <option value=\"departments\">Departments</option>\n    <option value=\"orders\">Orders</option>\n    <option value=\"products\">Products</option>\n  </select>\n\n  <label for=\"join-condition\">JOIN Condition (e.g. employees.dept_id = departments.id):</label>\n  <input type=\"text\" id=\"join-condition\" placeholder=\"\" aria-label=\"Join condition\" />\n\n  <label for=\"group-by\">GROUP BY columns (comma separated):</label>\n  <input type=\"text\" id=\"group-by\" placeholder=\"\" aria-label=\"GROUP BY columns\" />\n\n  <label for=\"having-condition\">HAVING Condition (e.g. COUNT(*) > 1):</label>\n  <input type=\"text\" id=\"having-condition\" placeholder=\"\" aria-label=\"HAVING condition\" />\n\n  <label for=\"order-by\">ORDER BY columns (comma separated, optionally with ASC/DESC):</label>\n  <input type=\"text\" id=\"order-by\" placeholder=\"\" aria-label=\"ORDER BY columns\"/>\n\n  <label for=\"limit-count\">LIMIT (number of rows, empty = no limit):</label>\n  <input type=\"text\" id=\"limit-count\" pattern=\"^[0-9]*$\" placeholder=\"\" aria-label=\"LIMIT count\" />\n\n  <button id=\"btn-build-query\">Build SQL Query From Controls</button>\n  <button id=\"btn-clear-controls\">Clear Controls</button>\n</div>\n</fieldset>\n\n<fieldset>\n  <legend>4. Tables Data</legend>\n  <label for=\"data-view-table\">Select table to view data:</label>\n  <select id=\"data-view-table\" aria-label=\"Select table to view data\">\n    <option value=\"employees\">Employees</option>\n    <option value=\"departments\">Departments</option>\n    <option value=\"orders\">Orders</option>\n    <option value=\"products\">Products</option>\n    <option value=\"custom\">Custom Table</option>\n  </select>\n  <button id=\"btn-view-table\">View Table Data</button>\n  <div id=\"table-data-container\" aria-live=\"polite\" style=\"margin-top:8px; max-height:300px; overflow:auto;\"></div>\n</fieldset>\n\n<fieldset>\n  <legend>5. Query Results</legend>\n  <div id=\"output\" tabindex=\"0\" aria-label=\"SQL query results and messages\">Run a query to see results here.</div>\n</fieldset>\n\n<script>\n(function(){\n  // In-memory example tables\n  const exampleTables = {\n    employees: {\n      name: 'employees',\n      columns: ['id', 'name', 'salary', 'dept_id'],\n      data: [\n        [1, 'John', 50000, 1],\n        [2, 'Alice', 60000, 2],\n        [3, 'Bob', 55000, 1],\n        [4, 'Diana', 70000, 3],\n        [5, 'Evan', 52000, 2],\n        [6, 'Fiona', 48000, null]\n      ],\n    },\n    departments: {\n      name: 'departments',\n      columns: ['id', 'dept_name', 'location'],\n      data: [\n        [1, 'Engineering', 'NY'],\n        [2, 'Marketing', 'CA'],\n        [3, 'Sales', 'TX'],\n      ],\n    },\n    orders: {\n      name: 'orders',\n      columns: ['order_id', 'cust_name', 'product_id', 'quantity', 'order_date'],\n      data: [\n        [101, 'John', 201, 2, '2022-12-01'],\n        [102, 'Alice', 202, 5, '2022-12-03'],\n        [103, 'Bob', 201, 1, '2022-12-05'],\n        [104, 'Alice', 203, 3, '2022-12-06'],\n        [105, 'John', 202, 4, '2022-12-10'],\n      ],\n    },\n    products: {\n      name: 'products',\n      columns: ['id', 'product_name', 'price'],\n      data: [\n        [201, 'Laptop', 1200],\n        [202, 'Mouse', 25],\n        [203, 'Keyboard', 45],\n        [204, 'Monitor', 250],\n      ],\n    }\n  };\n\n  // Store current loaded table\n  let currentTable = exampleTables.employees;\n  // Store custom table data\n  let customTable = {name:'custom', columns:[], data:[]};\n\n  // References for elements\n  const tableSelect = document.getElementById('table-select');\n  const customTableEditor = document.getElementById('custom-table-editor');\n  const customTableNameInput = document.getElementById('custom-table-name');\n  const customTableColsInput = document.getElementById('custom-table-cols');\n  const customTableDataTextarea = document.getElementById('custom-table-data');\n  const btnLoadCustomTable = document.getElementById('btn-load-custom-table');\n  const customTableStatus = document.getElementById('custom-table-status');\n\n  const sqlQueryTextarea = document.getElementById('sql-query');\n  const btnRunQuery = document.getElementById('btn-run-query');\n  const btnClearQuery = document.getElementById('btn-clear-query');\n  const btnResetAll = document.getElementById('btn-reset');\n\n  const selectColumnsInput = document.getElementById('select-columns');\n  const whereConditionsInput = document.getElementById('where-conditions');\n  const joinTypeSelect = document.getElementById('join-type');\n  const joinTableSelect = document.getElementById('join-table');\n  const joinConditionInput = document.getElementById('join-condition');\n  const groupByInput = document.getElementById('group-by');\n  const havingConditionInput = document.getElementById('having-condition');\n  const orderByInput = document.getElementById('order-by');\n  const limitCountInput = document.getElementById('limit-count');\n  const btnBuildQuery = document.getElementById('btn-build-query');\n  const btnClearControls = document.getElementById('btn-clear-controls');\n\n  const dataViewTableSelect = document.getElementById('data-view-table');\n  const btnViewTable = document.getElementById('btn-view-table');\n  const tableDataContainer = document.getElementById('table-data-container');\n\n  const outputDiv = document.getElementById('output');\n\n  // Very basic SQL parser and executor for selected constructs\n  // Supports only one table or one join max for demo purposes\n  // No INSERT/UPDATE/DELETE, only SELECT queries\n  // SQL supported parsing:\n  // SELECT columns FROM table [JOIN ... ON ...] [WHERE ...] [GROUP BY ...] [HAVING ...] [ORDER BY ...] [LIMIT ...]\n\n  // ---- UTILS ----\n\n  function cloneArrayDeep(arr) {\n    return arr.map(r => r.slice());\n  }\n\n  function stringifyValue(val) {\n    if (val===null || val===undefined) return 'NULL';\n    if (typeof val === 'string') return val;\n    return String(val);\n  }\n\n  // Case-insensitive startsWith\n  function ciStartsWith(str, part) {\n    return str.toLowerCase().startsWith(part.toLowerCase());\n  }\n\n  function trimSemi(str){\n    return str.trim().replace(/;$/,'');\n  }\n\n  // Tokenize a clause to array by commas outside of quotes and parentheses\n  function splitByCommas(str) {\n    let arr = [];\n    let current = '';\n    let parens = 0;\n    let inQuotes = false;\n    for (let c of str) {\n      if (c === \"'\" && (current.slice(-1) !== '\\\\')) inQuotes = !inQuotes;\n      if (!inQuotes) {\n        if (c === '(') parens++;\n        else if (c === ')') parens--;\n      }\n      if (c === ',' && !inQuotes && parens === 0) {\n        arr.push(current.trim());\n        current = '';\n      } else {\n        current += c;\n      }\n    }\n    if (current.trim()) arr.push(current.trim());\n    return arr;\n  }\n\n  // Parse simple condition expressions into functions\n  // Supports basic: col op value, combined by AND, OR (no parenthesis support)\n  // op: =, !=, <>, >, <, >=, <=, LIKE, IS NULL / IS NOT NULL\n  // value may be number, string literal ('..'), or identifier (and match exact)\n  // For demo, does NOT support SQL functions\n  function parseWhereWhereToFn(whereStr, tableAliasToColumns) {\n    if (!whereStr || !whereStr.trim()) return () => true;\n\n    // Tokenize by \" AND \", \" OR \" case insensitive and parse separately, for demo only AND supported robustly\n    // We'll support AND only for demo to keep complexity manageable\n    const andParts = whereStr.split(/(?<!\\\\)\\s+AND\\s+/i).map(s=>s.trim());\n    // Parse each part to function\n    const conditionFns = andParts.map(parseSimpleCondition);\n\n    // Join with AND\n    return function(row, rowOther, rowJoinType){\n      // row: object col name -> value, rowOther for join second table\n      // rowJoinType optional string for join side (for future expansion)\n      for(let fn of conditionFns){\n        if(!fn(row,rowOther,rowJoinType)) return false;\n      }\n      return true;\n    };\n\n    // Parse simple condition without AND/OR\n    function parseSimpleCondition(cond){\n      // Examples:\n      // salary > 50000\n      // employees.dept_id = departments.id\n      // name LIKE 'Al%'\n      // dept_id IS NULL\n      // dept_id IS NOT NULL\n      // col = 'string'\n      // col != 10\n      // col <> 10\n      // For demo, assumes col on left, value on right\n\n      let m;\n\n      // IS NULL, IS NOT NULL\n      if(m = cond.match(/^([\\w\\.]+)\\s+IS\\s+(NOT\\s+)?NULL$/i)){\n        const col = m[1];\n        const isNot = m[2]?true:false;\n        return (row,rowOther)=>{\n          let val = valFromCol(row,rowOther,col);\n          return isNot ? val !== null && val !== undefined : val === null || val === undefined;\n        };\n      }\n      // LIKE pattern (supports % wildcard)\n      if(m = cond.match(/^([\\w\\.]+)\\s+LIKE\\s+'(.+)'$/i)){\n        const col = m[1];\n        const patternRaw = m[2];\n        // Escape regex special chars except % => replace % with .* and _ with .\n        // Simplified for demo (no _ support)\n        let regexStr = '^' + patternRaw.replace(/[-/\\\\^$+?.()|[\\]{}]/g,'\\\\$&').replace(/%/g, '.*') + '$';\n        const regex = new RegExp(regexStr, 'i');\n        return (row,rowOther)=>{\n          let val = valFromCol(row,rowOther,col);\n          if (typeof val !== 'string') return false;\n          return regex.test(val);\n        };\n      }\n      // General comparison =, !=, <>, >=, <=, >, <\n      if(m = cond.match(/^([\\w\\.]+)\\s*(=|!=|<>|>=|<=|>|<)\\s*(.+)$/i)){\n        const col = m[1];\n        const op = m[2];\n        let valRaw = m[3].trim();\n\n        // valRaw may be number, string literal or identifier (col)\n        let valCmp;\n        let cmpCol = null;\n\n        if (/^'.*'$/.test(valRaw)) {\n          valCmp = valRaw.slice(1,-1).replace(/\\\\'/g,\"'\");\n        } else if (/^\\d+(\\.\\d+)?$/.test(valRaw)) {\n          valCmp = Number(valRaw);\n        } else {\n          // assume identifier col\n          cmpCol = valRaw;\n        }\n\n        return (row,rowOther)=>{\n          let val1 = valFromCol(row,rowOther,col);\n          let val2 = cmpCol? valFromCol(row,rowOther, cmpCol) : valCmp;\n\n          switch(op){\n            case '=': return val1 == val2;\n            case '!=':\n            case '<>': return val1 != val2;\n            case '>': return val1 > val2;\n            case '<': return val1 < val2;\n            case '>=': return val1 >= val2;\n            case '<=': return val1 <= val2;\n          }\n          return false;\n        };\n      }\n      // If no recognized pattern, always true\n      return ()=>true;\n    }\n\n    // Helper to get value from row or rowOther by colName which can have table alias prefix optionally\n    function valFromCol(row,rowOther,colName) {\n      if (!colName) return null;\n      let parts = colName.split('.');\n      if (parts.length === 1) {\n        // just col\n        return row[colName];\n      } else if(parts.length === 2){\n        // table.col\n        let [tbl, col] = parts;\n        if(rowOther && tbl === 't2') return rowOther[col];\n        if(row && tbl === 't1') return row[col];\n        // fallback: if rowOther is join table and tbl matches join table name in lowercase\n        if(rowOther && rowOther._tableName && rowOther._tableName.toLowerCase() === tbl.toLowerCase()) return rowOther[col];\n        if(row && row._tableName && row._tableName.toLowerCase() === tbl.toLowerCase()) return row[col];\n        // fallback if not found return null\n        return null;\n      }\n      return null;\n    }\n  }\n\n  // Parse ORDER BY clause string into array of {col, dir}\n  function parseOrderBy(orderStr) {\n    if (!orderStr) return [];\n    let parts = splitByCommas(orderStr);\n    return parts.map(p=>{\n      let m = p.match(/^(\\w+)(\\s+(ASC|DESC))?$/i);\n      if(!m) return null;\n      return {col:m[1], dir: m[3]?m[3].toUpperCase():'ASC'};\n    }).filter(x=>x);\n  }\n\n  // Aggregate functions implementation\n  // Supports COUNT([*]), SUM(col), AVG(col), MIN(col), MAX(col)\n  // col can be simple col name or *\n  // rows is array of row objects\n  // Returns value or null\n  function aggregateFunc(funcName, col, rows) {\n    let values;\n    funcName = funcName.toUpperCase();\n    if(funcName==='COUNT'){\n      if(col === '*') return rows.length;\n      values = rows.map(r=>r[col]).filter(v=>v!==null && v!==undefined);\n      return values.length;\n    }\n    values = rows.map(r=>r[col]).filter(v=>typeof v === 'number');\n    if(values.length === 0) return null;\n    switch(funcName){\n      case 'SUM': \n        return values.reduce((a,b) => a+b, 0);\n      case 'AVG':\n        return values.reduce((a,b) => a+b, 0) / values.length;\n      case 'MIN':\n        return Math.min(...values);\n      case 'MAX':\n        return Math.max(...values);\n    }\n    return null;\n  }\n\n  // Parse SELECT columns: supports aggregate funcs, col names, aliases (alias as col)\n  // Returns array of {expr, alias, isAggregate} where expr is original string\n  function parseSelectColumns(selectStr) {\n    if(!selectStr) return [{expr:'*', alias:'*', isAggregate:false}];\n    let parts = splitByCommas(selectStr);\n    return parts.map(p=>{\n      // possible: COUNT(*), SUM(salary), col, col AS alias, col alias (space), AVG(salary) as avg_sal\n      // We'll parse very basic\n      let m = p.match(/^(.+?)\\s+(?:AS\\s+)?(\\w+)$/i);\n      let expr = p.trim();\n      let alias = null;\n      if(m){\n        expr = m[1].trim();\n        alias = m[2].trim();\n      }\n      // Check if aggregate function\n      let isAggregate = /^(\\w+)\\s*\\(.+\\)$/.test(expr);\n      return {expr, alias: alias||expr, isAggregate};\n    });\n  }\n\n  // Given rows array and columns array, extract requested columns and output array of objects\n  // Supports aggregate functions ONLY in select columns\n  // For simplicity, no complex expressions, just col or agg func\n  function projectColumns(rows, selectCols, groupByCols) {\n    // rows: array of objects col->val\n    // selectCols: array {expr, alias, isAggregate}\n    // groupByCols: array of columns, or empty\n\n    if(selectCols.length===1 && selectCols[0].expr==='*' && !groupByCols.length){\n      // No selection, just output all columns in rows\n      return rows;\n    }\n\n    if(groupByCols.length){\n      // Group rows by groupByCols, and compute aggregates where needed\n      let groups = {};\n      for(let row of rows){\n        let key = groupByCols.map(c=>stringifyValue(row[c])||'NULL').join('|');\n        if(!groups[key]) groups[key] = [];\n        groups[key].push(row);\n      }\n      let result = [];\n      for(let groupKey in groups){\n        let groupRows = groups[groupKey];\n        let outRow = {};\n        for(let c of groupByCols) {\n          outRow[c] = groupRows[0][c];\n        }\n        for(let sc of selectCols){\n          if(groupByCols.includes(sc.alias) || groupByCols.includes(sc.expr)) continue; // already set\n          if(sc.isAggregate){\n            // parse func\n            let m = sc.expr.match(/^(\\w+)\\s*\\((.+)\\)$/);\n            if(m){\n              let func = m[1];\n              let col = m[2].trim();\n              if(col === '') col='*';\n              outRow[sc.alias] = aggregateFunc(func, col, groupRows);\n            } else {\n              outRow[sc.alias] = null;\n            }\n          } else {\n            // Non-aggregate columns not in group must be excluded in standard SQL.\n            // Set as null here for safety.\n            outRow[sc.alias] = null;\n          }\n        }\n        result.push(outRow);\n      }\n      return result;\n    } else{\n      // No group by - if aggregates present, aggregate over all rows single row\n      let hasAgg = selectCols.some(sc=>sc.isAggregate);\n      if(hasAgg){\n        let outRow = {};\n        for(let sc of selectCols){\n          if(sc.isAggregate){\n            let m = sc.expr.match(/^(\\w+)\\s*\\((.+)\\)$/);\n            if(m){\n              let func = m[1];\n              let col = m[2].trim();\n              if(col === '') col='*';\n              outRow[sc.alias] = aggregateFunc(func, col, rows);\n            } else {\n              outRow[sc.alias] = null;\n            }\n          } else {\n            // Columns without aggregation in aggregated query set null\n            outRow[sc.alias] = null;\n          }\n        }\n        return [outRow];\n      } else {\n        // Just project columns directly for each row\n        return rows.map(row=>{\n          let outRow = {};\n          for(let sc of selectCols){\n            if(sc.expr==='*'){\n              for(let c in row) outRow[c] = row[c];\n            } else {\n              outRow[sc.alias] = row[sc.expr];\n            }\n          }\n          return outRow;\n        });\n      }\n    }\n  }\n\n  // ORDER BY implementation\n  // rows: array of objects\n  // orders: array of {col, dir}\n  function orderByRows(rows, orders) {\n    if(!orders || !orders.length) return rows;\n    // create compare function\n    function cmp(a,b){\n      for(let ord of orders){\n        let va = a[ord.col];\n        let vb = b[ord.col];\n        if(va == null && vb != null) return -1;\n        if(vb == null && va != null) return 1;\n        if(va == null && vb == null) continue;\n        if(va < vb) return ord.dir === 'ASC' ? -1 : 1;\n        if(va > vb) return ord.dir === 'ASC' ? 1 : -1;\n      }\n      return 0;\n    }\n    return rows.slice().sort(cmp);\n  }\n\n  // Limit rows\n  function limitRows(rows, limit) {\n    if(!limit) return rows;\n    let n = Number(limit);\n    if(isNaN(n) || n < 0) return rows;\n    return rows.slice(0,n);\n  }\n\n\n  // ----------- SQL EXECUTOR DEMO ----------------\n\n  // Parse a limited SQL SELECT query and execute, returning results or error string\n  // Supports:\n  // SELECT ... FROM <table> [JOIN <type> <table> ON <condition>] [WHERE ...] [GROUP BY ...] [HAVING ...] [ORDER BY ...] [LIMIT ...];\n  // Only single join allowed max, table names must match our in-memory tables\n  function parseAndExecQuery(sql) {\n    outputDiv.textContent = '';\n    const sqlTrim = trimSemi(sql);\n    if(!ciStartsWith(sqlTrim,'select ')){\n      return {error:'Only SELECT queries supported.'};\n    }\n    // Basic regex to split clauses in order:\n    // SELECT (.+) FROM (\\w+) (optional JOIN) (optional WHERE) (optional GROUP BY) (optional HAVING) (optional ORDER BY) (optional LIMIT)\n    \n    // Build regex pattern to capture:\n    // SELECT ... FROM ... [JOIN type table ON cond] [WHERE ...] [GROUP BY ...] [HAVING ...] [ORDER BY ...] [LIMIT ...]\n    // all optional except SELECT and FROM\n\n    // To keep robust, parse manually by keywords sequentially:\n\n    let remaining = sqlTrim;\n\n    // Parse SELECT columns\n    let mSelect = remaining.match(/^select\\s+(.+?)\\s+from\\s+/i);\n    if(!mSelect) return {error:'Invalid SELECT/FROM clause.'};\n    let selectPart = mSelect[1].trim();\n    remaining = remaining.substr(mSelect[0].length - 5).trim(); // leave 'from '\n\n    // Parse FROM <table>\n    let mFrom = remaining.match(/^(\\w+)\\s*/i);\n    if(!mFrom) return {error:'Missing or invalid FROM clause.'};\n    let fromTableName = mFrom[1].toLowerCase();\n    remaining = remaining.substr(mFrom[0].length).trim();\n\n    // Get fromTable\n    let fromTable = null;\n    if(fromTableName === 'custom'){\n      if(customTable.columns.length === 0) return {error:'Custom table is empty. Define it first.'};\n      fromTable = {...customTable};\n    } else if (exampleTables[fromTableName]){\n      fromTable = {...exampleTables[fromTableName]};\n    } else {\n      return {error:'Unknown table \"' + fromTableName + '\" in FROM clause.'};\n    }\n\n    // Parse optional JOIN\n    let join = null;\n    if(ciStartsWith(remaining, 'inner join ') || ciStartsWith(remaining, 'left join ') || ciStartsWith(remaining, 'right join ') || ciStartsWith(remaining, 'full outer join ') || ciStartsWith(remaining, 'full join ')) {\n      // detect join type and table\n      // join regex for demo: (INNER|LEFT|RIGHT|FULL( OUTER)?) JOIN (\\w+) ON ([^ ]+)\n      let mJoin = remaining.match(/^(inner|left|right|full)(\\s+outer)?\\s+join\\s+(\\w+)\\s+on\\s+(.+?)(?=\\s+(where|group by|having|order by|limit|$))/i);\n      if(!mJoin) return {error:'Invalid JOIN clause or syntax.'};\n\n      let joinType = mJoin[1].toLowerCase();\n      if(joinType == 'full' && mJoin[2]) joinType = 'full outer';\n      let joinTableName = mJoin[3].toLowerCase();\n      let joinCondition = mJoin[4].trim();\n\n      // Adjust remaining\n      remaining = remaining.substr(mJoin[0].length).trim();\n\n      // Get join table\n      let joinTable = null;\n      if(joinTableName === 'custom'){\n        if(customTable.columns.length === 0) return {error:'Custom table is empty. Define it first.'};\n        joinTable = {...customTable};\n      } else if(exampleTables[joinTableName]){\n        joinTable = {...exampleTables[joinTableName]};\n      } else {\n        return {error:'Unknown join table \"' + joinTableName + '\".'};\n      }\n\n      join = {\n        type: joinType,\n        table: joinTable,\n        condition: joinCondition\n      };\n    }\n\n    // Parse optional WHERE, GROUP BY, HAVING, ORDER BY, LIMIT\n    let wherePart = '', groupByPart = '', havingPart = '', orderByPart = '', limitPart = '';\n\n    // function to extract clause by keyword\n    function extractClause(str, keyword, nextKeywords) {\n      let regex = new RegExp('\\\\b' + keyword + '\\\\b', 'i');\n      let found = str.match(regex);\n      if(!found) return [null, str];\n\n      let startIdx = found.index + keyword.length;\n      // find next keyword position:\n      let nextIdx = str.length;\n      for(let nk of nextKeywords) {\n        let m = str.toLowerCase().indexOf(' ' + nk.toLowerCase() + ' ', startIdx);\n        if(m !== -1 && m < nextIdx) nextIdx = m;\n        // also consider keywords at end without spaces before e.g. 'where xxx' at end?\n        if(str.toLowerCase().endsWith(nk.toLowerCase())) nextIdx = Math.min(nextIdx, str.length);\n      }\n      let cl = str.substring(startIdx, nextIdx).trim();\n      let rem = str.substring(nextIdx).trim();\n      return [cl, rem];\n    }\n\n    [wherePart, remaining] = extractClause(remaining, 'where',['group by', 'having', 'order by', 'limit']);\n    [groupByPart, remaining] = extractClause(remaining, 'group by',['having', 'order by', 'limit']);\n    [havingPart, remaining] = extractClause(remaining, 'having',['order by', 'limit']);\n    [orderByPart, remaining] = extractClause(remaining, 'order by',['limit']);\n    [limitPart, remaining] = extractClause(remaining, 'limit',[]);\n\n    // ------------------------\n\n    // Convert data rows array -> array of objects with keys from columns for easier querying\n    function arrayToObjects(table) {\n      let objs = [];\n      for(let r of table.data){\n        let obj = {};\n        for(let i=0;i<table.columns.length;i++){\n          obj[table.columns[i]] = r[i];\n        }\n        // Tag name for joins\n        obj._tableName = table.name;\n        objs.push(obj);\n      }\n      return objs;\n    }\n\n    let baseRows = arrayToObjects(fromTable);\n    let joinedRows;\n\n    if(join){\n      let joinRows = arrayToObjects(join.table);\n      try {\n        joinedRows = applyJoin(baseRows, joinRows, join.type, join.condition);\n      } catch(e){\n        return {error:'Error processing JOIN: ' + e.message};\n      }\n    } else {\n      joinedRows = baseRows.map(r=>Object.assign({}, r));\n    }\n\n    // Filtering WHERE clause condition\n    let whereFn = parseWhereWhereToFn(wherePart);\n\n    let filteredRows = joinedRows.filter(row => whereFn(row));\n\n    // Parse SELECT columns for projection + aggregation\n    let selectCols = parseSelectColumns(selectPart.trim());\n\n    // Parse GROUP BY columns\n    let groupByCols = [];\n    if(groupByPart && groupByPart.trim()) {\n      groupByCols = groupByPart.split(',').map(c=>c.trim()).filter(c=>c);\n    }\n\n    // Project columns + aggregate\n    let projectedRows;\n    try {\n      projectedRows = projectColumns(filteredRows, selectCols, groupByCols);\n    } catch(e) {\n      return {error:'Error during projection or aggregation: ' + e.message};\n    }\n\n    // Apply HAVING clause (after group)\n    if(havingPart && havingPart.trim()){\n      let havingFn = parseWhereWhereToFn(havingPart);\n      projectedRows = projectedRows.filter(row => havingFn(row));\n    }\n\n    // ORDER BY columns parse\n    let orders = parseOrderBy(orderByPart);\n\n    let orderedRows = orderByRows(projectedRows, orders);\n\n    // LIMIT\n    let limitedRows = limitRows(orderedRows, limitPart);\n\n    return {resultRows: limitedRows};\n  }\n\n  // Apply join of two row sets given join type and ON condition\n  // joinType: inner, left, right, full outer\n  // joinCondition: string condition to evaluate against pairs of rows, use row1 and row2 col names\n  function applyJoin(rows1, rows2, joinType, joinCondition){\n    const condFn = parseWhereWhereToFn(joinCondition);\n\n    let result = [];\n\n    // For full outer join keep track of matched right rows\n    let matchedRightIndices = new Set();\n\n    if(joinType==='inner'){\n      for(let r1 of rows1){\n        for(let r2 of rows2){\n          if(condFn(r1,r2)){\n            result.push({...r1, ...r2});\n          }\n        }\n      }\n    } else if(joinType==='left'){\n      for(let r1 of rows1){\n        let matched = false;\n        for(let r2 of rows2){\n          if(condFn(r1,r2)){\n            result.push({...r1, ...r2});\n            matched = true;\n          }\n        }\n        if(!matched){\n          let pad = {};\n          for(let c of rows2[0] ? Object.keys(rows2[0]) : []){\n            pad[c] = null;\n          }\n          result.push({...r1, ...pad});\n        }\n      }\n    } else if(joinType==='right'){\n      for(let r2 of rows2){\n        let matched = false;\n        for(let r1 of rows1){\n          if(condFn(r1,r2)){\n            result.push({...r1, ...r2});\n            matched = true;\n          }\n        }\n        if(!matched){\n          let pad = {};\n          for(let c of rows1[0] ? Object.keys(rows1[0]) : []){\n            pad[c] = null;\n          }\n          result.push({...pad, ...r2});\n        }\n      }\n    } else if(joinType==='full' || joinType==='full outer'){\n      let matchedLeft = new Set();\n      let matchedRight = new Set();\n      for(let i=0;i<rows1.length;i++){\n        for(let j=0;j<rows2.length;j++){\n          if(condFn(rows1[i],rows2[j])){\n            result.push({...rows1[i], ...rows2[j]});\n            matchedLeft.add(i);\n            matchedRight.add(j);\n          }\n        }\n      }\n      // left unmatched\n      for(let i=0;i<rows1.length;i++){\n        if(!matchedLeft.has(i)){\n          let pad = {};\n          for(let c of rows2[0] ? Object.keys(rows2[0]) : []){\n            pad[c] = null;\n          }\n          result.push({...rows1[i], ...pad});\n        }\n      }\n      // right unmatched\n      for(let j=0;j<rows2.length;j++){\n        if(!matchedRight.has(j)){\n          let pad = {};\n          for(let c of rows1[0] ? Object.keys(rows1[0]) : []){\n            pad[c] = null;\n          }\n          result.push({...pad, ...rows2[j]});\n        }\n      }\n    } else {\n      throw new Error('Unsupported join type: '+joinType);\n    }\n\n    return result;\n  }\n\n  // ------------------------\n\n  // Display result rows as a HTML table or message in output\n  function displayResults(result) {\n    if(result.error) {\n      outputDiv.textContent = 'Error: ' + result.error;\n      return;\n    }\n    let rows = result.resultRows || [];\n    if(rows.length === 0) {\n      outputDiv.textContent = 'Query executed successfully. No rows returned.';\n      return;\n    }\n    // Get columns (union of all keys)\n    let colsSet = new Set();\n    for(let r of rows){\n      Object.keys(r).forEach(k=>colsSet.add(k));\n    }\n    let cols = Array.from(colsSet);\n\n    // Build table text grid\n    let headerLine = cols.join(' | ');\n    let separatorLine = cols.map(c=>'='.repeat(c.length)).join('|');\n\n    // Align and padding\n    // To keep simple monospace, just space separated\n    // Create string output + a minimal table below\n\n    // Plain text output\n    let textOut = headerLine + '\\n' + separatorLine + '\\n';\n    for(let r of rows){\n      let line = cols.map(c=>{\n        let v = r[c];\n        if(v===null || v===undefined) return 'NULL';\n        if(typeof v === 'string') return v;\n        return v.toString();\n      }).join(' | ');\n      textOut += line + '\\n';\n    }\n\n    outputDiv.textContent = textOut;\n  }\n\n  // Display any selected table's data in #table-data-container in plain HTML table\n  function displayTableData(table) {\n    if(!table){\n      tableDataContainer.textContent = 'No data to display.';\n      return;\n    }\n    if(!table.columns || table.columns.length===0){\n      tableDataContainer.textContent = 'Table has no columns.';\n      return;\n    }\n\n    if(!table.data || table.data.length===0){\n      tableDataContainer.textContent = 'Table is empty.';\n      return;\n    }\n\n    let html = '<table id=\"table-data\" aria-label=\"Table data\"><thead><tr>';\n    for(let c of table.columns){\n      html += '<th>' + c + '</th>';\n    }\n    html += '</tr></thead><tbody>';\n    for(let r of table.data){\n      html += '<tr>';\n      for(let v of r){\n        html += '<td>' + (v===null || v===undefined ? 'NULL' : String(v)) + '</td>';\n      }\n      html += '</tr>';\n    }\n    html += '</tbody></table>';\n    tableDataContainer.innerHTML = html;\n  }\n\n  // Reset all inputs\n  function resetAll(){\n    tableSelect.value = 'employees';\n    customTableEditor.style.display = 'none';\n    customTableNameInput.value = '';\n    customTableColsInput.value = '';\n    customTableDataTextarea.value = '';\n    customTableStatus.textContent = '';\n    currentTable = exampleTables.employees;\n    sqlQueryTextarea.value = '';\n    clearControls();\n    dataViewTableSelect.value = 'employees';\n    displayTableData(exampleTables.employees);\n    outputDiv.textContent = 'Run a query to see results here.';\n  }\n\n  // Clear interactive controls\n  function clearControls(){\n    selectColumnsInput.value = '*';\n    whereConditionsInput.value = '';\n    joinTypeSelect.value = 'none';\n    joinTableSelect.value = '';\n    joinConditionInput.value = '';\n    groupByInput.value = '';\n    havingConditionInput.value = '';\n    orderByInput.value = '';\n    limitCountInput.value = '';\n  }\n\n  // Build SQL query from controls and place in textarea\n  function buildQueryFromControls(){\n    let sel = selectColumnsInput.value.trim()||'*';\n    let from = tableSelect.value==='custom' ? (customTableNameInput.value.trim() || 'custom') : tableSelect.value.trim();\n    let sql = 'SELECT ' + sel + ' FROM ' + from;\n    let joinType = joinTypeSelect.value;\n    let joinTbl = joinTableSelect.value;\n    let joinCond = joinConditionInput.value.trim();\n    if(joinType !== 'none' && joinTbl && joinCond){\n      let joinStr = joinType.toUpperCase();\n      if(joinStr === 'FULL') joinStr = 'FULL OUTER';\n      sql += ' ' + joinStr + ' JOIN ' + joinTbl + ' ON ' + joinCond;\n    }\n    let whereStr = whereConditionsInput.value.trim();\n    if(whereStr) sql += ' WHERE ' + whereStr;\n    let groupByStr = groupByInput.value.trim();\n    if(groupByStr) sql += ' GROUP BY ' + groupByStr;\n    let havingStr = havingConditionInput.value.trim();\n    if(havingStr) sql += ' HAVING ' + havingStr;\n    let orderByStr = orderByInput.value.trim();\n    if(orderByStr) sql += ' ORDER BY ' + orderByStr;\n    let limitStr = limitCountInput.value.trim();\n    if(limitStr) sql += ' LIMIT ' + limitStr;\n    sqlQueryTextarea.value = sql;\n  }\n\n  // Initialize select-columns default\n  selectColumnsInput.value = '*';\n\n  // Event listeners\n\n  tableSelect.addEventListener('change', e=>{\n    if(tableSelect.value === 'custom'){\n      customTableEditor.style.display = 'block';\n    } else {\n      customTableEditor.style.display = 'none';\n      currentTable = exampleTables[tableSelect.value] || exampleTables.employees;\n    }\n  });\n\n  btnLoadCustomTable.addEventListener('click', e=>{\n    let tName = customTableNameInput.value.trim();\n    let colsStr = customTableColsInput.value.trim();\n    let dataStr = customTableDataTextarea.value.trim();\n\n    if(!tName){\n      customTableStatus.textContent = 'Please enter a table name.';\n      return;\n    }\n    if(!colsStr){\n      customTableStatus.textContent = 'Please enter columns (comma separated).';\n      return;\n    }\n    let cols = colsStr.split(',').map(s=>s.trim()).filter(s=>s);\n    if(cols.length === 0){\n      customTableStatus.textContent = 'At least one column is required.';\n      return;\n    }\n    let dataLines = dataStr.split('\\n').filter(l=>l.trim().length>0);\n    let data = [];\n    for(let line of dataLines){\n      let parts = line.split(',').map(s=>s.trim());\n      if(parts.length !== cols.length){\n        customTableStatus.textContent = 'Row length mismatch for line: \"'+line+'\"';\n        return;\n      }\n      // For simplicity, parse numbers or leave strings\n      let row = parts.map(v=>{\n        if(v === 'NULL' || v === '') return null;\n        if(!isNaN(v)) return Number(v);\n        return v;\n      });\n      data.push(row);\n    }\n    customTable = {name: tName, columns: cols, data: data};\n    currentTable = customTable;\n    customTableStatus.textContent = 'Custom table \"'+tName+'\" loaded successfully.';\n    dataViewTableSelect.value = 'custom';\n  });\n\n  btnRunQuery.addEventListener('click', e=>{\n    let sql = sqlQueryTextarea.value.trim();\n    if(!sql) {\n      outputDiv.textContent = 'Please enter a SQL query.';\n      return;\n    }\n    // Execute\n    try {\n      let res = parseAndExecQuery(sql);\n      displayResults(res);\n    } catch(ex) {\n      outputDiv.textContent = 'Error: ' + ex.message;\n    }\n  });\n\n  btnClearQuery.addEventListener('click', e=>{\n    sqlQueryTextarea.value = '';\n  });\n\n  btnResetAll.addEventListener('click', e=>{\n    resetAll();\n  });\n\n  btnBuildQuery.addEventListener('click', e=>{\n    buildQueryFromControls();\n  });\n\n  btnClearControls.addEventListener('click', e=>{\n    clearControls();\n  });\n\n  btnViewTable.addEventListener('click', e=>{\n    let tblName = dataViewTableSelect.value;\n    let tbl = null;\n    if(tblName === 'custom'){\n      tbl = customTable.columns.length > 0 ? customTable : null;\n    } else {\n      tbl = exampleTables[tblName] || null;\n    }\n    if(tbl) {\n      displayTableData(tbl);\n    } else {\n      tableDataContainer.textContent = 'No data available for table: ' + tblName;\n    }\n  });\n\n  // On page load default display selected table data\n  displayTableData(currentTable);\n\n  // Accessibility: make output focusable and announce updates\n  outputDiv.setAttribute('tabindex', '0');\n\n  // Initialize\n  resetAll();\n})();\n</script>\n</body>\n</html>"
